@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .rsg-wrap { padding: 0 1rem; }
  .rsg-tips { padding: 1.25rem 1.25rem; }
  .rsg-table thead th, .rsg-table tbody td { padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem; }
}
</style>

<section class="rsg-page" aria-label="Ring sizing">
  <div class="rsg-wrap">

    <header class="rsg-hero">
      <h1 class="rsg-hero__title">Ring sizing</h1>
      <p class="rsg-hero__lead">A ring should sit precisely — close enough to stay where it belongs, easy enough to slip past the knuckle. Here is how to measure at home, with our compliments.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="rsg-section">
      <h2 class="rsg-section__title">Method 1 — measure a ring you already own</h2>
      <div class="rsg-section__body">
        <p>The most reliable way, if you have a ring that fits the correct finger.</p>
        <ol class="rsg-steps">
          <li>Place the well-fitting ring flat on a ruler or measuring tape.</li>
          <li>Measure the <strong>inside diameter</strong> from edge to edge in millimetres.</li>
          <li>Compare your measurement to the size chart below to find the US size.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rsg-section">
      <h2 class="rsg-section__title">Method 2 — string or paper</h2>
      <div class="rsg-section__body">
        <p>If no ring is to hand, a thin strip of paper or non-stretchy string works just as well.</p>
        <ol class="rsg-steps">
          <li>Cut a thin strip of paper or piece of non-stretchy string.</li>
          <li>Wrap it snugly around the finger, just below the knuckle.</li>
          <li>Mark the point where the strip overlaps with a pen.</li>
          <li>Lay it flat and measure the length in millimetres — this is the circumference.</li>
          <li>Find your size in the chart below using the circumference column.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rsg-section">
      <h2 class="rsg-section__title">Size chart</h2>
      <div class="rsg-section__body">
        <p>All measurements are approximate. When in doubt, round up to the nearest half size.</p>
        <div class="rsg-table-wrap">
          <table class="rsg-table">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>US size</th><th>Inside diameter (mm)</th><th>Circumference (mm)</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>3</td><td>14.0</td><td>44.2</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3.5</td><td>14.4</td><td>45.2</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4</td><td>14.8</td><td>46.5</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4.5</td><td>15.2</td><td>47.8</td></tr>
              <tr><td>5</td><td>15.7</td><td>49.0</td></tr>
              <tr><td>5.5</td><td>16.1</td><td>50.3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>6</td><td>16.5</td><td>51.5</td></tr>
              <tr><td>6.5</td><td>16.9</td><td>52.8</td></tr>
              <tr><td>7</td><td>17.3</td><td>54.0</td></tr>
              <tr><td>7.5</td><td>17.7</td><td>55.3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>8</td><td>18.1</td><td>56.6</td></tr>
              <tr><td>8.5</td><td>18.5</td><td>57.8</td></tr>
              <tr><td>9</td><td>18.9</td><td>59.1</td></tr>
              <tr><td>9.5</td><td>19.4</td><td>60.3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>10</td><td>19.8</td><td>61.6</td></tr>
              <tr><td>10.5</td><td>20.2</td><td>62.8</td></tr>
              <tr><td>11</td><td>20.6</td><td>64.1</td></tr>
              <tr><td>11.5</td><td>21.0</td><td>65.3</td></tr>
              <tr><td>12</td><td>21.4</td><td>66.6</td></tr>
              <tr><td>12.5</td><td>21.8</td><td>67.9</td></tr>
              <tr><td>13</td><td>22.2</td><td>69.1</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rsg-section">
      <h2 class="rsg-section__title">From the atelier</h2>
      <div class="rsg-tips">
        <ul class="rsg-bullets">
          <li>Measure at the end of the day, when fingers are at their natural size.</li>
          <li>Avoid measuring with cold hands — fingers contract in cooler temperatures.</li>
          <li>Between two sizes, take the larger one. A ring should breathe.</li>
          <li>Wider bands fit more snugly. For bands over 6 mm, size up by half.</li>
          <li>If the size proves wrong, our complimentary first resizing is offered within 30 days.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rsg-section">
      <h2 class="rsg-section__title">Frequently asked</h2>
      <div class="rsg-faq">

        <div class="rsg-faq__item">
          <button class="rsg-faq__q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">What if the size is wrong on arrival?</button>
          <div class="rsg-faq__a">
            <p>The first resizing is on us, within 30 days of delivery. Write to the atelier and we will arrange the exchange and shipping in both directions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rsg-faq__item">
          <button class="rsg-faq__q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">How do I size for a surprise proposal?</button>
          <div class="rsg-faq__a">
            <p>Borrow a ring they already wear on the relevant finger and measure its inside diameter in millimetres — or trace it on paper and send the tracing to us. We will help quietly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rsg-faq__item">
          <button class="rsg-faq__q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">Do wider bands fit differently?</button>
          <div class="rsg-faq__a">
            <p>Yes. Wider bands (over 6 mm) sit more snugly because they cover more of the finger. Take a half size up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What if the size is wrong on arrival?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The first resizing is complimentary within 30 days of delivery. Write to the atelier and we will arrange the exchange and shipping in both directions." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I size for a surprise proposal?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Borrow a ring they already wear on the relevant finger and measure its inside diameter in millimetres, or trace it on paper and send the tracing to us." } },
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do wider bands fit differently?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Wider bands (over 6 mm) sit more snugly because they cover more of the finger. Size up by half." } }
      ]
    }
    </script>

    <div class="rsg-cta">
      <p class="rsg-cta__text">Uncertain? Write to the atelier at <a href="mailto:hello@lauramilman.com">hello@lauramilman.com</a> and we will help.</p>
      <a href="/collections/engagement-rings" class="rsg-cta__link">Explore the collection &rarr;</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script>
(function () {
  var items = document.querySelectorAll('.rsg-faq__item');
  items.forEach(function (item) {
    var btn = item.querySelector('.rsg-faq__q');
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var open = item.classList.contains('is-open');
      items.forEach(function (i) {
        i.classList.remove('is-open');
        i.querySelector('.rsg-faq__q').setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      });
      if (!open) {
        item.classList.add('is-open');
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
      }
    });
  });
})();
</script>

